blue channel were dark, so they're closer to zero.

00:29:18.430 --> 00:29:20.380
And the green should be white.

00:29:20.380 --> 00:29:25.410
And in the area where your subject is, all of those
colors are the same or they're close to each other.

00:29:25.410 --> 00:29:26.490
They're the same in value.

00:29:26.490 --> 00:29:31.059
So when you subtract them and when you subtract
the red and the blue, what you get is a black

00:29:31.059 --> 00:29:33.579
in the center, because they were very close.

00:29:33.579 --> 00:29:36.879
And you get just a, kind of a little bit
darker gray because they were close to zero,

00:29:36.880 --> 00:29:39.760
so they're not subtracting very much from the green.

